PN,41602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1778234502
OL,3,CConservatives have the most to lose in
OL,4,Ctheir traditional southern heartlands
OL,6,FNo other party has ever had an
OL,7,Foutright majority on the three top-
OL,8,Ftier authorities, but could that
OL,9,Fchange for the last ever county
OL,10,Fcouncil election?
OL,12,FWhatever the result, it will be
OL,13,Fhistoric, the final poll before all
OL,14,Fexisting county and district councils
OL,15,Fin Sussex and Hampshire are abolished
OL,16,Fand replaced with new unitary
OL,17,Fauthorities as part of local
OL,18,Fgovernment reorganisation.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1778234502
OL,3,CConservatives have the most to lose in
OL,4,Ctheir traditional southern heartlands
OL,6,FThose reforms are the reason there
OL,7,Fwere so many local elections this May,
OL,8,Fafter scheduled county council votes
OL,9,Flast year were delayed by the Labour
OL,10,Fgovernment.
OL,12,FFor a time it looked like some
OL,13,Felections would be pushed back by
OL,14,Fanother year in Sussex, but a legal
OL,15,Fthreat from Reform UK forced a change
OL,16,Fof heart from ministers.
OL,18,FThe Conservatives currently have an
OL,19,Foutright majority on Hampshire and
OL,20,FWest Sussex county councils, and run a
OL,21,Fminority administration in East Sussex.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
