OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,417,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F416A1778234502
OL,3,CConservatives have the most to lose in
OL,4,Ctheir traditional southern heartlands
OL,6,FHampshire are counting their county
OL,7,Fcouncil ballots overnight, with a
OL,8,Ffinal result expected on Friday
OL,9,Fmorning. Both Sussex county councils
OL,10,Fare not due to finish their counts
OL,11,Funtil Friday evening.
OL,13,FIn a sign of the new multi-party
OL,14,Fpolitical environment, it is not just
OL,15,Fthe Tories facing a nervy wait for
OL,16,Fresults but Labour too.
OL,18,FSir Keir Starmer's party does not have
OL,19,Fa strong presence on county councils
OL,20,Fin the region, but does run several
OL,21,Fsmaller councils in urban areas.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/11
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
